New Records: Golden State Warriors survived in overtime as they edged past the Houston Rockets 127-121 at the Toyota Center on Saturday (Nov. 2).
Andrew Wiggins and Draymond Green contributed significantly with 15 and 14 points respectively.
Key Match Events: The Rockets fought back from a 28-point deficit to force overtime, tying 119-119 at the end of the fourth quarter.
Tari Eason and Jabari Smith Jr. were key contributors for the Rockets with 27 and 21 points respectively.
Others: The game took place on Nov. 2, a day before the scheduled matchup on Nov. 3.
